  "prompt": "What is uses of Die steel?",
  "response": "Die steel is a specialized type of steel used in various manufacturing and industrial applications, primarily for making dies, molds, and tools. Here are some key uses of die steel:\n\n1. Metal Forming\n- Stamping dies\n- Forging dies\n- Cutting tools\n- Punching tools\n\n2. Plastic Manufacturing\n- Injection molds\n- Compression molds\n- Extrusion dies\n\n3. Automotive Industry\n- Manufacturing automotive parts\n- Creating precision components\n- Tooling for vehicle production\n\n4. Precision Engineering\n- Machining tools\n- Cutting and shaping equipment\n- Measuring instruments\n\n5. Electronics Manufacturing\n- Circuit board fabrication\n- Semiconductor component production\n- Microchip manufacturing\n\n6. Aerospace Industry\n- Precision component manufacturing\n- Engine part production\n- Aircraft component fabrication\n\n7. Mechanical Engineering\n- Creating specialized mechanical parts\n- Designing complex machinery components\n- Manufacturing precision equipment\n\n8. Metallurgical Applications\n- Hot and cold working dies\n- Casting molds\n- Metalworking tools\n\n9. Medical Equipment Manufacturing\n- Surgical instrument production\n- Medical device components\n- Precision medical tools\n\nDie steel is chosen for its high hardness, wear resistance, and ability to maintain dimensional stability under high stress and temperature conditions.",
